The numbers are placed on a hexagonal spiral.  
For a hexagonal spiral the largest number in ring \(k\) is  

\[
N_{\max }(k)=1+3k(k+1)
\]

Hence

* ring 0 : \(1\)  
* ring 1 : ends at \(7\)  
* ring 2 : ends at \(19\) …  

---

### 1.  Find the ring of 2026  

Solve \(N_{\max }(k)\ge 2026\).

\[
1+3k(k+1)\ge 2026\Longrightarrow k^2+k-675\ge0
\]

\(k=26\) (since \(k=25\) gives \(N_{\max}=1951\)).  
So 2026 lies in ring \(k=26\).

The first number of ring 26 is  

\[
N_{\text{start}}(26)=N_{\max }(25)+1=1952 .
\]

The coordinate system (axial coordinates \( (q,r) \)) for a hexagonal spiral is taken as  

* start of ring \(k\) at \((k,0)\) (value \(N_{\text{start}}(k)\)),  
* then walk the six sides with direction vectors  

\[
\begin{aligned}
d_1&=(-1,1),\\
d_2&=(-1,0),\\
d_3&=(0,-1),\\
d_4&=(1,-1),\\
d_5&=(1,0),\\
d_6&=(0,1).
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### 2.  Coordinates of 2026  

From the start of the ring we move  

\[
2026-1952 = 74\quad\text{steps}.
\]

The first two sides consume \(2k=52\) steps, leaving \(22\) steps on the third side.
Thus  

\[
\begin{aligned}
\text{start}&:(26,0)\\
\text{after }d_1&:(0,26)\\
\text{after }d_2&:(-26,26)\\
\text{after }22\text{ steps of }d_3&:(-26,4).
\end{aligned}
\]

So 2026 is at \((-26,4)\).

---

### 3.  The six neighbours  

Adding the six direction vectors to \((-26,4)\) gives the neighbour coordinates  

\[
\begin{aligned}
(-25,4),\;(-25,3),\;(-26,3),\;(-27,4),\;(-27,5),\;(-26,5).
\end{aligned}
\]

Each coordinate belongs to a particular ring; using the same spiral‑construction we find the numbers at those coordinates.

| coordinate | ring | steps from start of that ring | number |
|------------|------|------------------------------|--------|
| \((-25,4)\) | 25 | \(25+25+21 = 71\) | \(1802+71 = 1873\) |
| \((-25,3)\) | 25 | \(25+25+22 = 72\) | \(1802+72 = 1874\) |
| \((-26,3)\) | 26 | \(26+26+23 = 75\) | \(1952+75 = 2027\) |
| \((-27,4)\) | 27 | \(27+27+23 = 77\) | \(2108+77 = 2185\) |
| \((-27,5)\) | 27 | \(27+27+22 = 76\) | \(2108+76 = 2184\) |
| \((-26,5)\) | 26 | \(26+26+21 = 73\) | \(1952+73 = 2025\) |

Thus the six neighbours of 2026 are  

\[
1873,\; 1874,\; 2027,\; 2025,\; 2184,\; 2185 .
\]

---

### 4.  Sum of the neighbours  

\[
\begin{aligned}
1873+1874+2027+2025+2184+2185 &= (1873+1874) + (2027+2025) + (2184+2185)\\
&= 3747 + 4052 + 4369\\
&= 12168 .
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
\boxed{12168}
\]
